      "author": {
        "_account_id": 124,
        "name": "Prakash Surya",
        "email": "lists@prakashsurya.com",
        "username": "prakash"
      },
      "date": "2011-03-28 16:14:42.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nSanity test 155{a,b,c,d} passed at LLNL:\n\n    * the minimum available size of OST > the large file size:\n    * https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/57735d48-5954-11e0-a272-52540025f9af\n\n    * the minimum available size of OST < the large file size:\n    * https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/a16b2974-5951-11e0-a272-52540025f9af",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "8bb737a59cb1b5805c430f0506d020392fc121a9",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 110,
        "name": "Chris Gearing",
        "email": "chris.gearing@intel.com",
        "username": "chris",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-03-28 16:38:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nMy code improvement would be that big is only declared in order to define large_file_size.\r\n\r\nBut [I've updated LU-160} if the OST it not big-enough the test has failed and so should fail indicating that the test failed because the OST was not big enough. This is correct and informative, the tester can then ask for the test to be positively skipped.\r\n\r\nIf the user asked for this test and it did not pass it should indicate fail.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "a5b9fa1aa7e7789d894c9a95863fb333ac275577",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 110,
        "name": "Chris Gearing",
        "email": "chris.gearing@intel.com",
        "username": "chris",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-03-28 16:39:42.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "04a030020a58789792982ec797b9eb7413287ac4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 131,
        "name": "Jian Yu",
        "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "yujian"
      },
      "date": "2011-03-29 07:50:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n>> But [I've updated LU-160} if the OST it not big-enough the \n>> test has failed and so should fail indicating that the\n>> test failed because the OST was not big enough. \nHow about moving the size check and skip codes to the position right before creating the large file by dd? In this case, if the OST is not big enough, the large file test would be skipped, otherwise the test would definitely fail with ENOSPC, which is not the purpose of test 155*.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
